  "prompt": "Which is Better: Raw egg or Boiled egg?",
  "response": "Both raw and boiled eggs have their pros and cons:\n\nBoiled Eggs:\n1. Safer to eat (kills harmful bacteria)\n2. Easier to digest\n3. Protein becomes more accessible\n4. Lower risk of salmonella\n5. Can be eaten hot or cold\n6. Better for those with sensitive stomachs\n\nRaw Eggs:\n1. Contain slightly more nutrients\n2. Protein is in its most natural state\n3. Faster to consume\n4. Often used in smoothies or protein shakes\n\nHowever, eating raw eggs carries significant health risks:\n- Higher chance of salmonella infection\n- Risk of food poisoning\n- Potential bacterial contamination\n\nRecommendation:\nMost health experts recommend eating boiled or cooked eggs to ensure safety and reduce health risks. If you want maximum nutrition, soft-boiled eggs can be a good compromise.",
